Dee Hibbert-Jones is an Academy Award-nominated, Emmy award-winning filmmaker and fine artist. Her animated films and installations (co-directed with Nomi Talisman) examine power and politics, how people manage and who gets heard. Hibbert-Jones is a Guggenheim Fellow, a MacDowell Fellow and was recently awarded a United States Congressional Black Caucus Veterans Braintrust Award in recognition for her “outstanding national commitment to civil rights, and social justice.” She is an Associate Professor of Art & Digital Art New Media at the University of California, Santa Cruz and founder/ co-director of SPARC at UCSC, a Social and Environmental Arts Research Center.
